FT  21 SEP 93 / International Company News: Spanish bank completes deal
BANCO Santander yesterday said its takeover bid for Portugal's Banco de
Comercio e Industria (BCI) had closed successfully. The Spanish bank's stake
in BCI is now up to 74.8 per cent from 19, AP-DJ reports from Madrid.
The bank paid Es1,400 a share for the stake, representing a premium of 40
per cent. It spent a total of Es21.1bn (Dollars 128m).
The bid was launched last May.
